#select based on users. get all user timestamp

user_list = glob.glob("/var/RIDER LOG/riderdata/*")

def read_data(user,date) :
    user_data_list = glob.glob([d for d in user_list if d[25:] == user][0]+"/*.csv")
    user_data_list = [d1 for d1 in user_data_list if d1[58:68] == date]
    data_list = []
    C_ = ["DATE","ACCEL_X","ACCEL_Y","ACCEL_Z","GYRO_X","GYRO_Y",
          "GYRO_Z","LAT","LON","ALT","ROLL","PITCH","VELOCITY","G_ACCEL_X","G_ACCEL_Y",
          "G_ACCEL_Z","EVENT0","EVENT1",'COL_ANGLE',"COL_MAG"]
    
    for csv1 in user_data_list :
        csv_data = pd.read_csv(csv1,header=None,names=C_)
        data_list.append(csv_data)
    ans_data = pd.concat(data_list)
    ans_data =  ans_data.reset_index(drop=True)
    return(ans_data)

In [178]:
#riders distance calculation
def riders(data):
    total_distance = 0
    for i in range(len(data)):
        if i != len(data)-1:
            temp1 = (data["LAT"].loc[i], data["LON"].loc[i])
            temp2 = (data["LAT"].loc[i+1], data["LON"].loc[i+1])
        else:
            temp1 = (data["LAT"].loc[i], data["LON"].loc[i])
            temp2 = (data["LAT"].loc[i], data["LON"].loc[i])
        distance = haversine(temp1, temp2, unit = 'km')
        total_distance = total_distance + distance
    return total_distance
